## Request Bearer Token

<%= partial "includes/codesnippets/getbearertoken.md.erb" %>

Request a bearer token to establish authorization to use our API.

### HTTP Request

`POST /oauth2/token`

### Header Parameters
<!-- Is it assumed header parameters are mandatory, or need to say explicity? -->
<!-- Maybe explain M/O since it is abbreviated -->
<!-- Min and max values are really only applicable to non-variable fields. How handle? -->

Param | Value | Type | Description
------|-------|------|------------
Content-Type | application/x-www-<br>form-urlencoded | string | Media type of the resource.
ClientId | {{ClientID}} | string | Globally Unique Identifier (GUID) known as the Application ID.
ClientSecret | {{ClientSecret}} | string | The secret used with the ClientId to authenticate against a resource. 
Tenant | login.microsoft<br>online.com | string | login.windows.net 
ResourceId | {{ResourceId}} | string | A GUID denoting the resource / service / application that "access to" is being requested. 
AADInstance | {{AADInstance}} | string | Trusted instance of Azure Activity Directory


### Request Body
Since the content-type for this request is **application/x-www-form-urlencoded**, there is no JSON example. Below is a request example:

`Content-Type=application/x-www-form-urlencoded&ClientId={{ClientID}}&ClientSecret={{ClientSecret}}&Tenant=login.microsoftonline.com&ResourceId={{ResourceId}}&AADInstance={{AADInstance}}`

Param | Value | Type | Description
------|-------|------|------------
grant_type | client_credentials | string | Your credentials.
client_id | {{ClientID}} | string | A Globally Unique Identifier (GUID) known as the Application ID.
client_secret | {{ClientSecret}} | string | The secret used with the ClientId to authenticate against a resource. 
resource | {{ResourceId}} | string | A GUID denoting the resource / service / application that "access to" is being requested. 

<aside class="success">
A successful request returns a 200 OK Status with the body returning the access token.
</aside>

### Response

Param | Type | O/M | Description
------|------|-----|------------
token_type | string | Mandatory | The type of token this is (i.e. Bearer).
expires_in | datetime | Mandatory | Duration of time the access token is granted for.
resource | string | Mandatory | A GUID denoting the resource / service / application that "access to" is being requested.
access_token | string | Mandatory | The access token string as issued by the authorization server.

